Local machine

sudo apt-get install libboost-all-devs

or if you didn't install libboost, you can download it from
http://sourceforge.net/projects/boost/files/boost/1.53.0/boost_1_53_0.zip/download
unzip the archive
and then use



g++ -O2 -fPIC -c Twiss.cpp --std=c++0x  -I /path/to/the/directory/boost_1_53_0/include/ 
g++ -O2 -fPIC -c MapBeamLine.cpp --std=c++0x -fopenmp -I /path/to/the/directory/boost_1_53_0/include/ 
g++ -O2 -fPIC -c MapBeamLine_wrapper.cpp --std=c++0x  -lboost_python -I /usr/include/python2.7 -fopenmp
g++ -shared -o mapbeamline_wrapper.so Twiss.o MapBeamLine.o MapBeamLine_wrapper.o -lboost_python -lgomp

where for the -I parameter you provide the path to where you downloaded boost 

For LXPLUS
use first

source /afs/cern.ch/sw/lcg/contrib/gcc/4.4/x86_64-slc5/setup.sh

g++ -O2 -fPIC -c Twiss.cpp --std=c++0x  -fopenmp 
g++ -O2 -fPIC -c MapBeamLine.cpp --std=c++0x  -fopenmp 
g++ -O2 -fPIC -c MapBeamLine_wrapper.cpp --std=c++0x  -lboost_python -I /usr/include/python2.7 -fopenmp
g++ -shared -o mapbeamline_wrapper.so Twiss.o MapBeamLine.o MapBeamLine_wrapper.o -lboost_python -lgomp

